    "reasoning": "The problem requires finding the constant $ k $ such that $ f_1(x) = \sqrt{x^2 + 6k} $. Given $ f_1(x) = \sqrt{x^2 + 48} $, equating the constants under the square root gives $ 6k = 48 $, so $ k = 8 $. This value of $ k $ determines the minimum distance between spectators as $ k - 7 = 1 $ meter.

For the Street Art Show, the key is analyzing how the distance $ KP_n $ grows with $ n $. Conditions (i) and (ii) require all spectators to be at least 10 meters from $ K $ and at least 1 meter apart. Condition (iii) ensures each new spectator chooses the closest possible position to $ K $, minimizing $ KP_n $.

In 2D packing, the number of points $ n $ that can fit within a circle of radius $ R $ with minimum pairwise distance $ d $ scales with the area $ \pi R^2 $. For large $ n $, the area required is proportional to $ n $, so $ R^2 \propto n $, implying $ R \propto \sqrt{n} $. Thus, $ KP_n $ grows proportionally to $ \sqrt{n} $, matching option (B). Options (A), (C), and (D) are inconsistent with 2D packing principles.",
